The paper deals with topic modeling of multimodal data using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper specifically applies the proposed model to image classification and annotation, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the Multimedia Information Retrieval (MIR) Flickr data set, indicating that cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as well.
